<br>
As I said, you logic is flawed, the only difference , as  you have clearly illustrated, is the amount of time between spawns.  For the record, a Ragefire can spawn sooner then a Guk Frenzy does.  Ragefire is variable.  I guess you are the offical designator of how much time it takes between spawns to determine what is and is not a camp?  Time is the only difference here, the only difference.  A person can wait an hour or 72 hours,, I have known dozens of people who have camped the frenzy for far longer.<br>
<br>
Lets do a step by step  analysis.  You go to the &quot;Frenzy&quot; camp, you clear all the mobs,, and what? wait for more to spawn, waiting for the named mob you hope to kill.<br>
You go to the &quot;ragefire&quot; camp, and what?  You kill all the mobs&lt;fire giants&gt; and wait for the named mob you want to kill to spawn.   Both cases you kill mobs as they respawn, only difference is the amount of time it might take for the named mob to actually surface.<br>
<br>
